### ============================================================================
### service-policy — FULL LIFECYCLE walkthrough (create → version → activate →
### evaluate → deactivate), with request AND response contracts for each step.
###
### Open in VS Code (REST Client) or IntelliJ HTTP Client; run top-down.
### Start the app first:  ./mvnw quarkus:dev    (Docker running for MongoDB + OIDC)
### Swagger UI: http://localhost:8080/q/swagger-ui   OpenAPI: /q/openapi
###
### Tokens (ADR-013):
###   {{admin_jwt}} — token whose role/scope satisfies the admin marker
###                   (default role "authz-admin"). Required for all /v1/policies* writes.
###   {{jwt}}       — any valid authenticated token. Used for /v1/evaluate.
###   See "How to obtain tokens" at the bottom.
###
### KEY CONCEPTS you'll exercise:
###   - Create leaves the policy INACTIVE. It is NOT evaluable until you activate it.
###   - Versions are append-only (PUT adds v2, v3…); you activate an EXPLICIT version.
###   - Writes are conditional: they need If-Match: "<revision>" (the ETag from a GET).
###       Stale ETag → 412 ; missing If-Match → 428.
###   - Errors are RFC 9457 application/problem+json (see docs/ERRORS.md).
### ============================================================================

@host = http://localhost:8080
@auth_admin = Bearer {{admin_jwt}}
@auth = Bearer {{jwt}}


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1) CREATE a policy  →  201 Created, INACTIVE
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Request: the full policy document. Response: PolicyCreated { policyId, version, active:false }.
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "policyId": "doc-access",
  "version": 1,
  "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
  "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": [
    { "id": "assigned-access", "effect": "PERMIT",
      "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "IN",
        "left": {"ref": "subject.id"}, "right": {"ref": "resource.attr.assignees"} } }
  ]
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  201 Created
### {
###   "policyId": "doc-access",
###   "version": 1,
###   "active": false            ← created inactive; not evaluable yet
### }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2) GET the policy  →  200, read the ETag (you need it to write)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK   (note the ETag response header)
### Headers:  ETag: "0"          ← revision counter; use it as If-Match below
### Body (PolicyHeadView):
### {
###   "policyId": "doc-access",
###   "resourceType": "document",
###   "activeVersion": null,      ← still inactive
###   "revision": 0,
###   "audit": { "createdBy": "<sub>", "createdAt": "…", "changeReason": null },
###   "activeContent": null       ← null while inactive
### }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3) APPEND a new version (PUT)  →  200, creates v2 (still inactive)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Requires If-Match with the current ETag ("0" from step 2).
### Body: { content: <full policy document>, changeReason }.
PUT {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "0"

{
  "content": {
    "policyId": "doc-access",
    "version": 2,
    "resourceType": "document",
    "actions": ["*"],
    "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
    "defaultEffect": "DENY",
    "rules": [
      { "id": "assigned-access", "effect": "PERMIT",
        "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "IN",
          "left": {"ref": "subject.id"}, "right": {"ref": "resource.attr.assignees"} } },
      { "id": "area-scope", "effect": "PERMIT",
        "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "EQ",
          "left": {"ref": "resource.attr.area"}, "right": {"ref": "subject.attr.area"} } }
    ]
  },
  "changeReason": "add area-scope rule"
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK
### Headers:  ETag: "1"          ← revision bumped 0 → 1
### Body: head view; activeVersion still null (append does not activate).


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4) LIST versions  →  200, see the history
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/versions
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK   (Paginated<PolicyVersionSummary>)
### {
###   "data": [
###     { "policyId": "doc-access", "version": 1, "resourceType": "document", "audit": {…} },
###     { "policyId": "doc-access", "version": 2, "resourceType": "document", "audit": {…} }
###   ],
###   "pagination": { "page": 1, "size": 20, "totalPages": 1, "totalElements": 2 }
### }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5) EVALUATE before activating  →  200 allowed:false (nothing is active)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Proves an inactive policy is invisible to /evaluate.
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1", "attributes": {"assignees": ["test-user"]}}
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK   (Decision)
### { "allowed": false, "reason": "…no active policy…", "decisionId": "<uuid>",
###   "policyVersion": null, "obligations": [] }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6) ACTIVATE version 2  →  200, now it's live
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Explicit version + If-Match with the current ETag ("1" from step 3).
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/activate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "1"

{
  "version": 2,
  "changeReason": "go live with area-scope"
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK
### Headers:  ETag: "2"          ← revision bumped 1 → 2
### Body (head view): activeVersion: 2, activeContent: <v2 document>


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 7) EVALUATE — PERMIT (subject is an assignee)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Replace "test-user" with the sub in your {{jwt}}.
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1", "attributes": {"assignees": ["test-user"]}}
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK
### { "allowed": true, "reason": "…assigned-access…", "decisionId": "<uuid>",
###   "policyVersion": 2, "obligations": [] }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 8) EVALUATE — PERMIT via area-scope (v2's new rule)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d2", "attributes": {"area": "A"}},
  "subjectAttributes": {"area": "A"}
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK  →  allowed: true (area matches)


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 9) EVALUATE — DEFAULT DENY (nothing matches)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d4", "attributes": {"assignees": ["someone-else"], "area": "B"}},
  "subjectAttributes": {"area": "A"}
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK  →  allowed: false (defaultEffect DENY)


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 10) BATCH evaluate  →  200, several decisions at once
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate/batch
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requests": [
    { "action": "document:read", "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1", "attributes": {"assignees": ["test-user"]}} },
    { "action": "document:read", "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d4", "attributes": {"area": "B"}}, "subjectAttributes": {"area": "A"} }
  ]
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK  →  { "decisions": [ {allowed:true,…}, {allowed:false,…} ] }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 11) DEACTIVATE  →  200, soft retire (history intact)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### If-Match with the current ETag ("2" from step 6).
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/deactivate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "2"

{ "changeReason": "temporarily retire" }

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK
### Headers:  ETag: "3"
### Body: activeVersion: null, activeContent: null (versions still exist)


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 12) EVALUATE after deactivate  →  200 allowed:false (back to no active policy)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1", "attributes": {"assignees": ["test-user"]}}
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK  →  allowed: false


### ============================================================================
### ERROR CONTRACTS — RFC 9457 application/problem+json (docs/ERRORS.md)
### Run these to see each failure shape.
### ============================================================================

### 13) 409 POLICY_ALREADY_EXISTS — create an id that already exists
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "policyId": "doc-access",
  "version": 1,
  "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
  "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": []
}

### EXPECTED  409  application/problem+json
### { "type": "…/ERRORS.md#policy-already-exists", "title": "Policy already exists",
###   "status": 409, "code": "POLICY_ALREADY_EXISTS", "detail": "…", "policyId": "doc-access" }


### 14) 428 PRECONDITION_REQUIRED — write without If-Match
PUT {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "content": { "policyId": "doc-access", "version": 3, "resourceType": "document",
    "actions": ["*"], "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES", "defaultEffect": "DENY", "rules": [] },
  "changeReason": "no if-match" }

### EXPECTED  428  code: "PRECONDITION_REQUIRED"


### 15) 412 PRECONDITION_FAILED — stale If-Match (use an old ETag like "0")
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/activate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "0"

{ "version": 1 }

### EXPECTED  412  code: "PRECONDITION_FAILED"  (extension: currentRevision)


### 16) 404 POLICY_NOT_FOUND — unknown id
GET {{host}}/v1/policies/does-not-exist
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  404  code: "POLICY_NOT_FOUND"


### 17) 404 VERSION_NOT_FOUND — activate a version that doesn't exist
### (first GET doc-access to read its current ETag, then use it here in place of "3")
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/activate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "3"

{ "version": 99 }

### EXPECTED  404  code: "VERSION_NOT_FOUND"


### 18) 400/422 INVALID_POLICY — ordering operator with a non-numeric LITERAL (ADR-023)
### GT against a string literal "abc" is rejected AT AUTHORING.
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "policyId": "bad-typed",
  "version": 1,
  "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
  "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": [
    { "id": "bad", "effect": "PERMIT",
      "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "GT",
        "left": {"ref": "subject.attr.clearance"}, "right": {"value": "abc"} } }
  ]
}

### EXPECTED  400  code: "INVALID_POLICY"
### { …, "code": "INVALID_POLICY", "invalidParams": [ { "field": "…", "reason": "…numeric…" } ] }
### NOTE (ADR-023): a non-numeric LITERAL is rejected here. A non-numeric ATTRIBUTE
### resolved at runtime (e.g. {"ref": "subject.attr.clearance"} that arrives as a string)
### is NOT an error — the comparison just doesn't hold → deny. /evaluate never returns 500.


### 19) 403 FORBIDDEN — write with a non-admin token
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "policyId": "nope", "version": 1, "resourceType": "document", "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES", "defaultEffect": "DENY", "rules": [] }

### EXPECTED  403  code: "FORBIDDEN"  (caller lacks the admin marker)


### ============================================================================
### CLEANUP (optional) — there is no hard delete by design (soft retire only).
### To reset, drop the Mongo collections in dev, or use a fresh policyId.
### ============================================================================

### ============================================================================
### HOW TO OBTAIN TOKENS (dev)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### In quarkus:dev the OIDC dev services start a Keycloak. Get tokens via the
### Dev UI (http://localhost:8080/q/dev) → OIDC, or via password grant against the
### dev realm. {{admin_jwt}} must carry the admin marker (role "authz-admin" by
### default; configurable per ADR-013). {{jwt}} is any authenticated user.
### Set @admin_jwt and @jwt at the top, or use your client's env/variables file.
###
### CONDITION REFERENCE (for authoring your own policies):
###   Operators: EQ, NEQ, IN, NOT_IN, GT, GTE, LT, LTE
###   Operands:  {"ref": "<path>"}   paths: subject.id | subject.attr.* |
###              resource.type | resource.id | resource.attr.* | context.*
###          or  {"value": <literal>}
###   Composites: {"type": "and"|"or", "conditions": [ … ]}
###   Ordering ops (GT/GTE/LT/LTE) require numeric operands (ADR-023).
### ============================================================================
